  "target_response": {
    "text": "Your 54% is low because all three of its main inputs ran on the wrong side of your history overnight, even though you feel fine — the score reads physiology, not mood. Ranked by impact from today's breakdown: first, HRV came in at 41 ms, about 11 ms below your 30-day baseline of 52 ms; second, your resting heart rate of 62 bpm sat about 4 bpm above its 30-day baseline of 58 bpm; third, you slept 6.5 h, about 1.2 h short of your 7.7 h need. Feeling fine while the numbers dip is common — subjective energy often lags physiology by a day. One lever for tonight: set lights-out early enough to clear that sleep gap, and let tomorrow's reading confirm the rebound.",
